                            <comment id="12843339" author="pkamath" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2010 22:48:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch re-enables TestCounters in build.xml. Since counters are broken in local mode (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1286&quot; title=&quot;Counters are broken in local mode (number of bytes written/number of records written)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1286&quot;&gt;PIG-1286&lt;/a&gt;), the testLocal method is commented out and in local mode the number of bytes/records written is reported as unknown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the results from running test-patch ant target locally:&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; +1 overall.  &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     +1 @author.  The patch does not contain any @author tags.&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     +1 tests included.  The patch appears to include 5 new or modified tests.&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     +1 javadoc.  The javadoc tool did not generate any warning messages.&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     +1 javac.  The applied patch does not increase the total number of javac compiler warnings.&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     +1 findbugs.  The patch does not introduce any new Findbugs warnings.&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;     +1 release audit.  The applied patch does not increase the total number of release audit warnings.&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;exec&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Am currently running all unit tests - will update with results on completion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12843341" author="pkamath" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2010 22:50:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The consolidates hadoop-0.20.2 jar for use as lib/hadoop20.jar along with the patch attached previously.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12843353" author="daijy" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2010 23:09:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Shall we also close &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1203&quot; title=&quot;Temporarily disable failed unit test in load-store-redesign branch which have external dependency&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12843359" author="pkamath" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2010 23:39:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes - I will close &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1203&quot; title=&quot;Temporarily disable failed unit test in load-store-redesign branch which have external dependency&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; when I resolve this issue after tests complete.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12843378" author="dvryaboy" created="Wed, 10 Mar 2010 00:33:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this make 0.7 incompatible with earlier versions of hadoop 0.20?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12843381" author="pkamath" created="Wed, 10 Mar 2010 00:40:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;0.20.2 is supposed to backward compatible with 0.20.1 - I am also running some tests on a 0.20.1 cluster to ensure that there are no failures due to incompatiblities.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12846199" author="pkamath" created="Tue, 16 Mar 2010 23:15:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new patch also fixes warning aggregation in PigHadoopLogger to use the counter support now available in hadoop 0.20.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12846287" author="hadoopqa" created="Wed, 17 Mar 2010 04:12:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;-1 overall.  Here are the results of testing the latest attachment &lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12438984/PIG-1287-2.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12438984/PIG-1287-2.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  against trunk revision 924034.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    +1 @author.  The patch does not contain any @author tags.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    +1 tests included.  The patch appears to include 5 new or modified tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    +1 javadoc.  The javadoc tool did not generate any warning messages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    +1 javac.  The applied patch does not increase the total number of javac compiler warnings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    +1 findbugs.  The patch does not introduce any new Findbugs warnings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    +1 release audit.  The applied patch does not increase the total number of release audit warnings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    -1 core tests.  The patch failed core unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    +1 contrib tests.  The patch passed contrib unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test results: &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Pig-Patch-h7.grid.sp2.yahoo.net/240/testReport/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Pig-Patch-h7.grid.sp2.yahoo.net/240/testReport/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
